&lt;h1&gt;Summary:&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking for a great opportunity? Come join our team at an HVAC manufacturer representative firm. S. Conley Sales has been serving the needs of the HVAC industry in several of the fastest-growing communities in Montana and Wyoming with a culture focused on being Trustworthy, Committed, Resilient, Generous, and Humble. For over 24 years, our team has built a strong reputation that provides us opportunities to partner with the key manufacturers, engineers, facility owners, and contractors in the Mountain West Region. S Conley Sales continually strives to be recommended first by our customers. We know where we are choosing to win, how we win, and with what capabilities and systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our home base is in Bozeman, Montana. &amp;nbsp;S. Conley encourages our people to grow professionally and contribute to a strong and growing team, while building a meaningful life that aligns your personal goals with those of our company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Master Service Technician is responsible for performing detailed startup and service on millions of dollars of HVAC equipment being installed into the market on a yearly basis. Equipment such as Air Handlers, Chillers, Boilers, Pumps, Refrigerant Split Systems, VRF, VFD’s, Heat Pumps, Fans, Cooling Towers, Packaged Rooftop Units, DOAS, UV, Controls and more. You will work hand in hand with our Service Manager, fellow lead technicians, the manufacturer, and our local product experts. As our face to the customer in the field, you will often be the last person on the project. In this role, you are responsible for making sure the equipment is operating correctly and that we are handing over a quality final product to the customer, with the intent to keep and develop long-term customer relationships. This position will require travel throughout the states of Montana and Wyoming. An outfitted company service truck will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is the expectation that a Master Technician will work to help educate and teach our younger technicians on skills and technical problem solving that you have developed over the last 15 + years.&amp;nbsp; You will work with our technicians as a mentor and help them resolve issues as they are working in the field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Factory training will be provided, with the expectation you will be the local certified technician for the manufacturers represented by S Conley Sales. Expanded opportunities exist for an entrepreneur-minded technician who wants to take ownership in the growth of an excellent division of our company.&lt;/p&gt;
